The 2016 WGC-HSBC Champions was a &lt;a href="golf"&gt;golf&lt;/a&gt; tournament played from 27–30 October 2016 at the &lt;a href="Sheshan%20Golf%20Club"&gt;Sheshan Golf Club&lt;/a&gt; in &lt;a href="Shanghai"&gt;Shanghai&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href="China"&gt;China&lt;/a&gt;. It was the eighth &lt;a href="WGC-HSBC%20Champions"&gt;WGC-HSBC Champions&lt;/a&gt; tournament, and the fourth of four &lt;a href="World%20Golf%20Championships"&gt;World Golf Championships&lt;/a&gt; events held in the 2016 calendar year.
&lt;a href="Hideki%20Matsuyama"&gt;Hideki Matsuyama&lt;/a&gt; won by 7 strokes from &lt;a href="Daniel%20Berger%20%28golfer%29"&gt;Daniel Berger&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href="Henrik%20Stenson"&gt;Henrik Stenson&lt;/a&gt;. Matsuyama became the first Japanese golfer to win an individual World Golf Championship.
